>ow about UHMW?It is used in industrial applications for bushings and drive 
>chain guides.It also is FDA approved so you can feel good setting your 
>beer or favorite beverage on it.In the food industry our prep tabletops 
>were made from it.It also makes excellant slider pucks for your motorcycle 
>leathers,why buy cheap ones that wear easily when you can get a sheet of 
>UHMW and sticky back velcro for the same price.We made some nice case 
>guards from it as well.
>
>
>http://www.altavista.com/sites/search/web?q=UHMW&pg=q&avkw=tgz&kl=XX
>
> From a web site:
>
>UHMW possesses a unique combination of physical and mechanical properties 
>which enable it to perform well under the most rigorous conditions of wear 
>and environment. It has the highest known impact strength of any 
>thermoplastic presently made, plus high resistance to abrasion against a 
>wide variety of metals. These properties make UHMW an exceptional material 
>for industrial impact, wear and sliding operations. UHMW is FDA compliant 
>and USDA approved for direct contact in food processing applications.

